nodes.name: mutehelp
formdata:
Make sure you have the "monke" role at the highest position
(otherwise it might not work properly)
MUTE COMMAND
1. Go to the Server Settings
2. Go to the Roles tab
3. Find the 'muted' role
4. Disable all Text Permissions abilities

Your bot is now set up! :D

embedfields.name: ```kick```
embedfields.value: will kick the @'ed member until they rejoin

embedfields.name: ```ban```
embedfields.value: will permanently kick the @'ed member from the server

embedfields.name: ```purge```
embedfields.value: will delete the number of messages you specify (max 100)

embedfields.name: ```mute```
embedfields.value: will prevent an @'ed member from speaking in a channel

embedfields.name: ```unmute```
embedfields.value: reallows an @'ed member to speak if previously muted

embedfields.name: ```infractions```
embedfields.value: checks the number of infractions of an @'ed member

embedfields.name: ```monke```
embedfields.value: a random image of a monke :D

embedfields.name: ```cap```
embedfields.value: use this if someone is cappin'

embedfields.name: ```bruh```
embedfields.value: use when there is a bruh moment
